						               													<description>During the Ottoman rule of the Bulgarian lands, the hajduks (&amp;#208;&amp;#165;&amp;#208;&amp;#176;&amp;#208;&amp;#185;&amp;#208;&amp;#180;&amp;#209;&amp;#131;&amp;#209;&amp;#130;&amp;#208;&amp;#184;), thousands of unwavering men and women would embark on the terrible, but glorious path to freedom.&amp;#10;In the 1860s and 1870s, when the game is set, the Bulgarian revolutionary movement was at its peak.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There are three game modes - short, medium and long. Three important indicators of the game must be monitored - Recruitment, Activity and Combat Power. They are all tracked on the &amp;quot;committee board&amp;quot; in front of each player. The Winner of &amp;#208;&amp;#165;&amp;#208;&amp;#176;&amp;#208;&amp;#185;&amp;#208;&amp;#180;&amp;#209;&amp;#131;&amp;#209;&amp;#130;&amp;#208;&amp;#184; will be the one who gathers the most powerful detachment of freedom fighters, which depends on the strength of his committee. &amp;#10;During a turn, players can choose different types of revolutionaries, form groups and encounter Ottoman guards, all done in a certain order. Also, they will be able to recruit real Bulgarian historical figures, like Vasil Levski, who have skills inspired by their life path.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
